-- Hong Kong Air Pollution Hits `Very High' at Three Stations for Second Day
-- B y   T a t i a n a   L a u
-- 2010-12-01T06:32:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/hong-kong-air-pollution-very-high-at-three-stations-update1-.html
Hong Kong’s Environmental Protection
Department  reported  “very high” air pollution at the city’s
three roadside stations this morning for the second straight day.  The Air Pollution Index was 141 in Central, 104 in Causeway
Bay and 105 in Mong Kok as of 12 p.m., the department said on
its website.  Readings above 100 trigger a government  warning  for people
with heart or respiratory ailments to avoid prolonged stays in
heavy traffic areas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Tatiana Lau  in Hong Kong at 
 tlau29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
